  "prompt": "How do I book a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride?",
  "response": "To book a round trip on Uber and have it counted as a single ride, you can utilize Uber's \"Add multiple stops\" feature. This allows you to include both your outbound and return journeys within one trip request. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you set this up:\n\n1. **Open the Uber App:**\n   - Ensure you're logged into your Uber account on your smartphone.\n\n2. **Set Your Pickup Location:**\n   - The app will typically default to your current location. If not, enter the desired pickup point.\n\n3. **Enter Your First Destination:**\n   - Tap on the \"Where to?\" box and input your initial destination (e.g., from Home to the Airport).\n\n4. **Add a Return Trip as a Second Stop:**\n   - After entering the first destination, look for an option like \"Add stop\" or a \"+\" icon usually located beneath the destination field.\n   - Tap on it and enter your return trip destination (e.g., from Airport back to Home).\n\n5. **Review Your Trip:**\n   - Ensure both destinations are correctly listed. The trip should now show both stops in sequence.\n\n6. **Choose Your Ride Type:**\n   - Select the Uber service that best fits your needs (e.g., UberX, UberXL, etc.).\n\n7. **Confirm and Request:**\n   - Once everything is set, tap on \"Confirm\" or \"Request\" to book the ride.\n\n8. **Communicate with Your Driver (Optional but Recommended):**\n   - After requesting, you might receive driver details. It's a good practice to inform them about the round trip plan to ensure they're aware of the schedule and stops.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Time Considerations:** Make sure to account for the time needed at your first destination to avoid making your driver wait longer than expected.\n  \n- **Fare Estimates:** The fare will be calculated based on the total distance and time of both legs of the trip. Ensure you\u2019re comfortable with the estimated price before confirming.\n\n- **Availability:** The \"Add multiple stops\" feature may not be available in all regions or for all types of Uber services. If you don't see the option, you might need to book two separate rides instead.\n\n- **Alternative Options:** If you frequently require round trips, consider booking a return trip in advance if Uber offers scheduled rides in your area. Alternatively, discuss with local drivers about ongoing arrangements if that fits within Uber\u2019s policies.\n\nBy following these steps, you can efficiently manage a round trip within Uber as a single ride, simplifying your travel and potentially saving on booking separate trips.",
